# Queues and Cron Jobs

## BullMQ queues (app/server/queues)

- backupQueue.ts — handles backups (paired with tasks/backup API and cron)
- plaidSyncQueue.ts — primary Plaid sync processing
- plaidSyncBalanceQueue.ts — Plaid balance-only syncs
- recalculateQueue.ts — schedule recalculation/forecast updates

Queue orchestration helpers in server/lib/queueManager.ts and server/clients/queuesClient.ts. Admin flag SHOW_BULL_MQ_ADMIN controls visibility of bull-board in production environment (set to false in deploy template by default).

## Cron (nuxt-cron) jobs (app/server/cron)

- backup.daily.ts — periodic backups
- bill-reminders.hourly.ts — evaluate and send bill reminders
- plaid.daily.ts, plaid-balance.hourly.ts — Plaid sync cadence
- recalculate.hourly.ts — periodic recalculation tasks
- crypto-balance.hourly.ts — sync crypto balances via AlchemyService

Cron jobs should be idempotent. For long-running work, enqueue jobs rather than running synchronously.

## Task endpoints (app/server/api/tasks)

- backup.ts, migrate.ts (internal), recalculate.ts, sync-all.ts
- check-* and test-* endpoints exist for diagnostics in controlled environments
- sync-google-sheet*.post.ts — spreadsheet import helpers

